genes <- c("CCL18", "CCL19", "CCL2", "CCL21", "CCL3", "CCL4", "CCL5", "CCL8", "CXCL10", "CXCL11", "CXCL11_2", "CXCL13", "CXCL9")

Immune Response Dominated by Myeloid and B Cells (Goff CCR 2022)

NanoString followed by clustering with KEGG pathway analysis.
Signatures: cell proliferation, myeloid inflammatory, B cells, Ag presentation, NK cells https://aacrjournals.org/view-large/figure/14118087/1701fig5.jpeg

genes.df <- data.frame(geneName = c("ANXA2", "BRAF", "BRIC5", "MKI67",
                     "CXCL2", "S100A8", "S100A9",
                     "HLA-DMA", "HLA-DMB", "HLA-DPB1", "HLA-DRA", "CD14", "CD86", "MRC1", "MARCO", "ITGAM", "CTSB", "CTSS", "FCGR2B",
                     "FCGR2B", "LILRB4", "SYK",
                     "SYK", "HCST", "HLA-G", "TYROBP"),
             pathway = c(rep("Cell proliferation",4),
                         rep("Myeloid inflammatory",3),
                         rep("Agpresentation",12),
                         rep("B cells",3),
                         rep("NK cells",4)))
genes <- rowData(SEobj) %>% as.data.frame %>% filter(geneName %in% genes.df$geneName) # %>% select(geneName, gene_id)
genes <- merge(genes,genes.df)
for (n in unique(genes.df$pathway)) {
  signatures[[paste0("Goff_",n)]] <- genes[which(genes.df$pathway==n),"gene_id"]

IFNy signature and Expanded immune signature (Ayers, McClanahan 2017)

This 28-gene set encompassed genes related to cytolytic activity (e.g., granzyme A/B/K, PRF1), cytokines/chemokines for initiation of inflammation (CXCR6, CXCL9, CCL5, and CCR5), T cell markers (CD3D, CD3E, CD2, IL2RG [encoding IL-2R]), NK cell activity (NKG7, HLA-E), antigen presentation (CIITA, HLADRA), and additional immunomodulatory factors (LAG3, IDO1, SLAMF6)

Signature score with GSVA from the previous gene sets

sig.mat <- gsva(SEobj, signatures, 'vst', method='gsva', kcdf="Gaussian", parallel.sz=8, mx.diff=F, tau=1, verbose=params$verbose)
sehm(sig.mat[,order(SEobj$MENOPAUSAL_STATUS)], rownames(sig.mat),assayName="es", do.scale=TRUE, anno_columns = "MENOPAUSAL_STATUS", 
     cluster_cols = params$cluster_cols, cluster_rows = T, show_colnames = T, anno_colors = list(MENOPAUSAL_STATUS=c(premenopausal="green3", menopausal="red2"))) # , anno_rows="meanTPM"

design <- model.matrix(~0+factor(sig.mat$MENOPAUSAL_STATUS))
colnames(design) <- c("menopausal", "premenopausal")
design
##    menopausal premenopausal
## 1           1             0
## 2           1             0
## 3           1             0
## 4           1             0
## 5           0             1
## 6           0             1
## 7           0             1
## 8           0             1
## 9           1             0
## 10          1             0
## 11          1             0
## 12          1             0
## attr(,"assign")
## [1] 1 1
## attr(,"contrasts")
## attr(,"contrasts")$`factor(sig.mat$MENOPAUSAL_STATUS)`
## [1] "contr.poly"
cont_matrix <- makeContrasts(PostvsPre = menopausal-premenopausal, levels = design)
cont_matrix
##                Contrasts
## Levels          PostvsPre
##   menopausal            1
##   premenopausal        -1
# Fit the expression matrix to a linear model
fit <- lmFit(assay(sig.mat), design)
# Compute contrast
fit_contrast <- contrasts.fit(fit, cont_matrix)
# Bayes statistics of differential expression
# *There are several options to tweak!*
fit_contrast <- eBayes(fit_contrast)
# Generate a vocalno plot to visualize differential expression
volcanoplot(fit_contrast)

# Generate a list of top 100 differentially expressed genes
top_genes <- topTable(fit_contrast, number = 100, adjust = "BH")
# Summary of results (number of differentially expressed genes)
result <- decideTests(fit_contrast)
summary(result)
##        PostvsPre
## Down           0
## NotSig        23
## Up             0
top_genes

Which version of MSigDB was used?

This package was generated with MSigDB v7.5.1 (released January 2022). The MSigDB version is used as the base of the msigdsbr package version. You can check the installed version with packageVersion(msigdbr).

hallmarks <- msigdbr(species = "Homo sapiens", category = "H")
if(params$verbose) table(hallmarks$gs_name)
signatures_H <- list()
for (n in unique(hallmarks$gs_name)) {
  signatures_H[[n]] <- hallmarks %>% filter(gs_name==n) %>% pull("ensembl_gene") 
}
sig.mat.H <- gsva(SEobj, signatures_H, 'vst', method='gsva', kcdf="Gaussian", parallel.sz=8, mx.diff=F, tau=1, verbose=params$verbose)
